AeroFTP Portable
================

This file marks the AeroFTP installation as a portable build.

Do not delete this file. It is required for:
  - in-place updates (the auto-updater detects portable mode via this marker)
  - portable data storage (config, cache, and logs are written next to the
    executable rather than in %APPDATA%)

If you delete this file by mistake, AeroFTP will fall back to standard
Windows data directories on the next launch and your in-place update
mechanism will revert to launching the NSIS installer.

To convert a portable install into a regular install, uninstall the portable
folder and run the official installer (.msi or setup.exe) from
https://github.com/axpdev-lab/aeroftp/releases.
